Systemic 
(noun)
1. a collective construct wherein each part serves the purpose of connecting and expanding upon the premise it seeks to express


(adjective)
1. that which has a specific relational essence as in being part of the whole
2. that which is linked in an organizational way as to be dependent on what follows and what it precedes
3. that which is to be understood as an interdependent which is part of the whole but also has an idenitity in and of itself
4. that which pertains to a process of development that is other than random
5. that which is defined by its structure as being an inter-related set of tenets which together explains, denotes, or expresses a prima tenet